Subject: [PATCH] NHAc recognition motif: bidentate arm in inverse design
 engine
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

parameters_v23.py:
  EPS_NHAC_MONO      = -4.5 kJ/mol  (single H-bond to NHAc C=O)
  EPS_NHAC_BIDENTATE = -9.5 kJ/mol  (NH donor + C=O acceptor engaged)
  NHAC_EPS dict: 'none'|'mono'|'bidentate'
  Source: Chervenak & Toone 1994 JACS 116:10533; WGA PDB 2UVO geometry
  STATUS: PROVISIONAL v2.4 — threshold analysis confirms EPS < -6.1
  kJ/mol required for GlcNAc selectivity at C2 vs Glc

inverse_design.py:
  PocketConfig gains nhac_arm: str field ('none'|'mono'|'bidentate')
  _score_pocket_sugar: NHAc arm logic
    - C2 + K_NAC sugar → apply NHAC_EPS bonus
    - C2 + OH sugar → arm does not engage (bonus=0); standard HB possible
    - C2 arm position excluded from generic n_HB count
  Enumeration: nhac_arm looped as new dimension when C2 in pocket

Results (bidentate arm, contacts [C2,C4], 1 HB, 3×Trp):
  GlcNAc: gap=-7.30 vs Man, -3.40 vs Glc/Gal  [grade A]
  GalNAc: gap=-7.30 vs Man, -3.40 vs Glc/Gal  [grade A]
          GalNAc/GlcNAc degenerate (C4 axial: additional handle needed)

Physics note: mono arm (-4.5) insufficient alone; bidentate (-9.5)
  required to overcome K_NAC burial penalty (+8.5 kJ/mol) at C2.
